Below is the documentation for the provided HTML and CSS code:

## HTML Code Documentation:

### `<!DOCTYPE html>`:
- This declaration specifies that the document is an HTML5 document.

### `<html lang="en">`:
- The opening tag for the HTML document with the language attribute set to "en" (English).

### `<head>`:
- Contains meta-information about the HTML document like character encoding, viewport settings, and the document title.

### `<meta charset="UTF-8">`:
- Specifies the character encoding for the document, set to UTF-8 (Unicode Transformation Format - 8 bits).

### `<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">`:
- Sets the viewport properties, ensuring that the content width adjusts to the device's width and initial-scale is set to 1.

### `<title>landing page</title>`:
- Sets the title of the HTML document, which appears in the browser tab.

### `<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="sty.css"/>`:
- Links an external CSS file named "sty.css" to the HTML document to apply styles.

### `<body>`:
- Contains the visible content of the HTML document.

### `<header>`:
- Represents the header section of the web page, usually containing navigation and other introductory elements.

### `<div class="main">`:
- A container div for the main content of the header.

### `<ul>`:
- An unordered list that holds the navigation links.

### `<li>`:
- Represents each item (link) in the unordered list.

### `<a href="#">`:
- The anchor tag that defines a hyperlink, with "#" as a placeholder for the link destination.

### `<div class="logo">`:
- A container div for the logo image.

### `<img src="ig2.png">`:
- The image tag that displays the logo with the source set to "ig2.png".

### `<div class="center_text">`:
- A container div for the centered text and buttons.

### `<h1>`:
- The heading tag used to define the main heading of the page.

### `<a href="#" id="bt1">Contact</a>` and `<a href="#" id="bt2">Read more.</a>`:
- Anchor tags representing hyperlinks with the text "Contact" and "Read more." The IDs are used to apply specific styles using CSS.

## CSS Code Documentation:

### `*{}`:
- Applies the following styles to all elements in the HTML document.

### `header{}`:
- Styles the header section, which includes the background image and height.

### `.main{}`:
- Styles the container for the main content of the header.

### `ul{}`:
- Styles the unordered list, removing the default list style.

### `ul li{}`:
- Styles each list item (link) in the unordered list, displaying them inline.

### `ul li a{}`:
- Styles the anchor tags within the list items, setting their color, display, and padding.

### `.active{}`:
- Styles the active (current) link in the navigation, changing its background color.

### `.logo img{}`:
- Styles the logo image, setting its height, width, and margins.

### `.center_text{}`:
- Styles the container for centered text and buttons, setting the margin and position.

### `h1{}`:
- Styles the main heading, setting its color and font size.

### `#bt1{}` and `#bt2{}`:
- Styles the contact and "Read more" buttons, setting their border, padding, text color, and font size.

### `#bt1:hover{}` and `#bt2:hover{}`:
- Styles the buttons when hovered over, changing their background color and text color with a smooth transition effect.

Overall, this HTML and CSS code create a simple landing page with a header containing a navigation bar, a logo, a centered heading, and two buttons. The page uses external CSS styles to customize the appearance and layout of the elements.
